if it is not possible to comply with paragraph (a), the sample must be
              obtained from the subsurface liquid in the separator as close as is practical to the
              point where the effluent enters the outlet pipe;

if there is any other configuration of effluent discharge where (a) and (b)
              above are not practical, the sampling method must be acceptable to a
              director.
